                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Minister of Foreign Relations of Nicaragua</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to acknowledge your telegram of the 22d of September. The
                    tributes of Nicaragua’s respect for the memory of President McKinley are deeply
                    appreciated by the American Government and people.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
